@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{i}Shania V1.0  @{ui}

 If you prefer working with a mouse and icons rather than text and keyboard
 than Shania is the program for you.
 If you not familiar with amigados but need you need to use a amigados command like
 assign then Shania will make a gui for you.
 
 GUI (Graphical User Interface) 
 A visually-oriented system allowing you to tell a computer what to do by manipulating
 graphic symbols.

@endnode

@node "System_Requirements" "System Requirements"

 @{i}Shania @{ui}needs:

 · A amigacomputer with Workbench 2.0 or better
 · Reqtools.library

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

 @{i}Installation @{ui}
 
 Installing @{i}Shania @{ui}is easy: just launch the supplied installer script!
 If you don't want to use the script you can just copy the Shania drawer wherever
 you want and copy the files in the libs drawer to the Libs:

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"

 @{i}Using @{ui}Shania...

 After you launch Shania you must choose a program to create a gui for.
 Shania will search for the program's plugin.
 If the plugin not exists but the program is using the amigados syntax then Shania will
 try to create a gui but you are on your one here...

 When the program guiwindow is active you can use the following functionkeys:

 F1 - Realtime mode On/Off
 DEL - Reset Shania.
 HELP - How to use...

 Click on the OK button when the command is ready.
 Now you can execute the command or place the command in the user-startup or clipboard.
  
@endnode



